On a side note, looking at the 16 to 17 age groups shows that some answers were erroneous. In France, the legal voting age is 18. Therefore, the 16 to 17 year olds, at least at the beginning of their service civique (q0/q1), have never possible voted legally before. However, as shown in @fig-vote_derniers_elections-youngest there are 443 volunteers who answered "no" at q0/q1 (which technically is true, but not the most specific answer option), and 20 who answered "yes" (probably not reading the question carefully or accidentally clicking on the wrong response). It is unclear whether or how this could have affected our findings on changes in voting behavior. 


